1 WHEREAS, in Oklahoma, the rate of rape and attempted rape among
2 females reported to law enforcement has been 35-45% higher than the
3 U.S. rate for the past decade; and
4 WHEREAS, Oklahoma law enforcement reported 2,245 forcible and
5 attempted rapes in 2020 - which represented 12.5% of all violent
6 crimes, and reported rape cases have increased 21% over the past 3
7 years, and 34.2% overall since 2013; and
8 WHEREAS, youth under 18 account for about 44% of all reported
9 sexual assaults, at least 25% of women experience sexual harassment
10 in the workplace and about 75% of sexual harassment victims
11 experience retaliation when they report it; and
12 WHEREAS, sexual violence and its unfair and traumatizing effects
13 are preventable with proper education on the matter and
14 comprehensive prevention projects; and
15 WHEREAS, members of the Oklahoma House of Representatives
16 strongly support the efforts of Peace Over Violence and the YWCA of
17 Oklahoma City to educate persons in our state about the true impact
18 of sexual harassment, abuse, assault and rape.
19 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
20 OF THE 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
21 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives recognizes the month
22 of April as Sexual Assault Awareness Month.
23 THAT the Oklahoma House of Representatives designates April 30,
24 2025, as Denim Day and urges everyone to wear jeans on this day to
